    "### Dataset #2: Higher Education Students’ Evolving Perceptions of ChatGPT\n",
    "  - **Dataset Name:** Higher Education Students’ Evolving Perceptions of ChatGPT: Global Survey Data from the Academic Year 2024–2025\n",
    "  - **Link to the dataset:** https://data.mendeley.com/datasets/nv2343nwsb/2\n",
    "  - **Number of observations:** 22,963 students from 120 countries/territories\n",
    "  - **Number of variables:** 175\n",
    "  - The variables most relevant to our project is the self-reported frequency of students using ChatGPT for the tasks listed in Q18. The sub-questions in Q18 can be grouped into three categories: assignment production, learning support, and both. Since the responses in the dataset have already converted into numbers corresponding to the rating scale from “Never” to “Always,” the average score of each category will be utilized to compare the frequency of using ChatGPT for learning support versus assignment production.\n",
    "      - Assignment production\n",
    "        - academic writing (Q18a) - `use_academic`\n",
    "        - professional writing (Q18b) - `use_professional`\n",
    "        - creative writing (Q18c) - `use_creative`\n",
    "        - proofreading (Q18d) - `use_proofreading`\n",
    "      - Learning support\n",
    "        - summarizing (Q18g) - `use_summarize`\n",
    "        - calculating help (Q18h) - `use_calculate`\n",
    "        - study assistance (Q18i) - `use_study`\n",
    "        - personal assistance (Q18j) - `use_personal`\n",
    "      - Both\n",
    "        - brainstorming (Q18e) - `use_brainstorm`\n",
    "        - translating (Q18f) - `use_translating`\n",
    "        - research assistance (Q18k) - `use_reseach`\n",
    "        - coding assistance (Q18l) - `use_coding`\n",
    "  - Similar to dataset #1, the survey results are entirely based on the student's perception and interpretation of the questionnaire, increasing the likelihood of dishonest responses and misunderstandings. With respect to the project, the data excludes underlying specific reasons why a student would use ChatGPT to complete those tasks, such as whether one uses it for the convenience, or due to the competitiveness of their academic environment, which potentially ties to the economic development of a country. Furthermore, this dataset lacks reports on the students’ financial circumstances. Therefore, we also need to incorporate datasets that display the economic development of the countries reported by the students in order to get a clearer visualization that can answer our questions."
   ]
