    "This project took a look at how students from around the world use Chat GPT for academic work and whether or not the economic GDP of their country was related to how often they use it and what they use it for. In the background section, we discussed how research already shows a growing usage of AI in various fields, such as agriculture, and our project builds on this by examining how Chat GPT is growing in relation to the academic sphere. We analyzed survey responses in regards to Chat GPT usage, students confidence, and explored whether economics might influence students Chat GPT usage.\n",
    "\n",
    "Our exploratory analysis revealed several consistent patterns across the datasets. Most students reported using Chat GPT occasionally or moderately for schoolwork, with relatively few students indicating extensive or constant use. Students appeared to rely slightly more on Chat GPT for help with learning activities, such as summarizing information, studying, or brainstorming ideas, than for producing assignments, such as generating essays or completing programming assignments. These patterns suggest that many students treat Chat GPT primarily as a learning aid rather than a full replacement for their academic work. This analysis also relies on the students to accurately reflect their Chat GPT usage, which could be affected by honesty or whether or not they understand their usage on the same scale as another student.\n",
